  "texts": [
    "\"C3 + DIN\" uses LangChain's SQL-Database module to access database metadata.",
    "This metadata is manipulated to represent the schema in an automated way.",
    "Clear Prompting (C3) + Schema Linking (DIN).",
    "C3 uses a prompt with much fewer tokens than DIN, that is, cheaper.",
    "Indeed, DIN considers all tables for schema linking and uses a chain-of-thought strategy (a series of intermediate reasoning steps) providing examples that assist the LLM during reasoning."
  ],
